overview: The user identified that their Vercel dashboard showed five projects
  for a single application, "sleep-questionnaire," which was causing confusion.
  I explained that this typically occurs when the same GitHub repository is
  imported multiple times into Vercel, creating new projects with random
  suffixes. The goal was to retain only the primary
  project and remove the four duplicates. I used the Vercel CLI to delete the
  duplicate projects. After an initial attempt to delete all at once with a
  flag failed, I proceeded to delete each of the four duplicate projects
  individually by piping "y" as confirmation to the  command.
  All duplicates were successfully removed, leaving the user with a clean Vercel
  dashboard showing only the intended project.
